      <speaker_name>Decanus</speaker_name>
      <npc_text>It takes you almost an hour to complete the ritual. When you push the last lever, the cave is filled with a low, grumbling noise and reddish light. Powered by the ancient magic somehow preserved within the tube, the machines come to life. They move slowly at first, the rusted metal resisting and screeching, but the magic releases oil from some hidden reservoirs. Soon, the machines are running almost as smoothly as they did in the olden days.

Unfortunately, they make enough noise to wake up the dead and within moments you're surrounded by the Aurelian guards.

"You're still alive because you've managed to get the machines working," explains the Decanus. "Lucky for you, I'm an ambitious man, and I hope to be well rewarded for delivering a &lt;man/woman&gt; of your skills to Lord Gaelius. You're going to Maadoran."</npc_text>
